  "chapter": {
    "number": 49,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "The Servant and Light to the Gentiles"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Listen to Me, O islands;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2677
          },
          {
            "text": "pay attention, O distant peoples:",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "The LORD called Me from the womb;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "from the body of My mother He named Me.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He made My mouth like a sharp sword;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "He hid Me in the shadow of His hand.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "He made Me like a polished arrow;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "He hid Me in His quiver.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He said to Me, “You are My Servant, Israel,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "in whom I will display My glory.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "But I said, “I have labored in vain,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I have spent My strength in futility and vanity;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "yet My vindication is with the LORD,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and My reward is with My God.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "And now says the LORD,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "who formed Me from the womb to be His Servant,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "to bring Jacob back to Him,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "that Israel might be gathered to Him—",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "for I am honored in the sight of the LORD,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and My God is My strength—",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He says: “It is not enough for You to be My Servant,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "to raise up the tribes of Jacob,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and to restore the protected ones of Israel.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "I will also make You a light for the nations,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "to bring My salvation to the ends of the earth.”",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2678
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Thus says the LORD,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the Redeemer and Holy One of Israel,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "to Him who was despised and abhorred by the nation,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "to the Servant of rulers:",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "“Kings will see You and rise,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and princes will bow down,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "because of the LORD, who is faithful,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the Holy One of Israel, who has chosen You.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          "This is what the LORD says:",
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "“In the time of favor I will answer You,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and in the day of salvation I will help You;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2679
          },
          {
            "text": "I will keep You and appoint You",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "to be a covenant for the people,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "to restore the land,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "to apportion its desolate inheritances,",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "to say to the prisoners, ‘Come out,’",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and to those in darkness, ‘Show yourselves.’",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "They will feed along the pathways,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and find pasture on every barren hill.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "They will not hunger or thirst,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "nor will scorching heat or sun beat down on them.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2680
          },
          {
            "text": "For He who has compassion on them will guide them",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and lead them beside springs of water.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I will turn all My mountains into roads,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and My highways will be raised up.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Behold, they will come from far away,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "from the north and from the west,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2681
          },
          {
            "text": "and from the land of Aswan.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2682
          },
          {
            "text": "”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Shout for joy, O heavens; rejoice, O earth;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "break forth in song, O mountains!",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "For the LORD has comforted His people,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and He will have compassion on His afflicted ones.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "But Zion said, “The LORD has forsaken me;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the Lord has forgotten me!”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "“Can a woman forget her nursing child,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "or lack compassion for the son of her womb?",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Even if she could forget,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I will not forget you!",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 16,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Behold, I have inscribed you on the palms of My hands;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "your walls are ever before Me.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 17,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Your builders",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2683
          },
          {
            "text": "hasten back;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "your destroyers and wreckers depart from you.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 18,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Lift up your eyes and look around.",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "They all gather together; they come to you.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "As surely as I live,” declares the LORD,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "“you will wear them all as jewelry",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and put them on like a bride.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 19,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For your ruined and desolate places",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and your ravaged land",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "will now indeed be too small for your people,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and those who devoured you will be far away.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 20,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Yet the children of your bereavement",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "will say in your hearing,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "‘This place is too small for us;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "make room for us to live here.’",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 21,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Then you will say in your heart,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "‘Who has begotten these for me?",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "I was bereaved and barren;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I was exiled and rejected.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "So who has reared them?",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Look, I was left all alone,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "so where did they come from?’”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 22,
        "content": [
          "This is what the Lord GOD says:",
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "“Behold, I will lift up My hand to the nations,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and raise My banner to the peoples.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "They will bring your sons in their arms",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2684
          },
          {
            "text": "and carry your daughters on their shoulders.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 23,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Kings will be your foster fathers,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and their queens your nursing mothers.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "They will bow to you facedown",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and lick the dust at your feet.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Then you will know that I am the LORD;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "those who hope in Me will never be put to shame.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 24,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Can the plunder be snatched from the mighty,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "or the captives of a tyrant",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2685
          },
          {
            "text": "be delivered?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 25,
        "content": [
          "Indeed, this is what the LORD says:",
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "“Even the captives of the mighty will be taken away,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the plunder of the tyrant will be retrieved;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "I will contend with those who contend with you,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and I will save your children.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 26,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I will make your oppressors eat their own flesh;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "they will be drunk on their own blood, as with wine.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Then all mankind will know that I, the LORD,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "am your Savior and your Redeemer,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "the Mighty One of Jacob.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
